message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. The paper discusses a system for answering complex questions in the tourism domain using natural language processing techniques, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The system also involves querying knowledge sources, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning models such as CRFs and LSTMs also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the system involves working with databases and structured query languages, which could be related to databases (cs.DB).
